1
00:00:06,983 --> 00:00:10,503
Hold the laryngoscope near the base,

2
00:00:11,350 --> 00:00:13,750
and slide it along the tongue.

3
00:00:14,110 --> 00:00:15,916
- Tube, please.
- Here.

4
00:00:17,470 --> 00:00:22,010
Guide the tube past the vocal cords
and place it in position.

5
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:28,200
I can do it fine on a dummy!

6
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,963
But with a real patient,
I freeze up and can't do it.

7
00:00:33,506 --> 00:00:36,420
Tamotsu, are you planning
to work in emergency medicine?

8
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:38,660
No way. Why?

9
00:00:39,022 --> 00:00:41,666
You're suddenly practicing and all.

10
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:47,263
I won't be an ER doc, but while I'm here,
I wanna be useful, you know?

11
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:53,086
I've never gotten it right, though.
Maybe there's a trick to it...

12
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,540
Why not ask Dr. Ashura?

13
00:00:56,020 --> 00:00:58,093
Asking someone skilled is the quickest way.

14
00:00:58,133 --> 00:00:59,360
True.

15
00:01:06,216 --> 00:01:09,456
Did you forget your promise?

16
00:01:24,916 --> 00:01:27,616
Huh? Where's she going?

17
00:01:35,790 --> 00:01:38,610
She's not supposed to leave
the hospital during shifts.

18
00:01:39,610 --> 00:01:41,410
Well, neither should I.

19
00:01:46,886 --> 00:01:48,089
Ramen?

20
00:01:49,415 --> 00:01:50,423
Oh well, whatever.

21
00:01:50,463 --> 00:01:51,870
I'll get her to treat me.

22
00:01:52,673 --> 00:01:53,902
Dr. Anno!

23
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:57,425
What a coincidence! Mind if I join you?

24
00:01:57,465 --> 00:01:58,673
Suit yourself.

25
00:02:06,317 --> 00:02:08,427
Do they not have a menu?

26
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:13,420
I only do omakase.

27
00:02:17,896 --> 00:02:20,496
Only omakase? Is that okay?

28
00:02:28,510 --> 00:02:31,616
Looks like regular ramen...

29
00:02:41,059 --> 00:02:43,043
This is insanely good.

30
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:45,910
So good!

31
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:53,930
Japan's God Hand saved
the global finance king's life!

32
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:59,470
As far as the public knows,
Dr. Bonten did the surgery alone.

33
00:03:00,203 --> 00:03:02,602
What? But Dr. Ashura was
the one who did it, right?

34
00:03:02,642 --> 00:03:04,935
Anno's name is nowhere to be found.

35
00:03:04,950 --> 00:03:07,710
But is it really okay
for them to publish this?

36
00:03:08,129 --> 00:03:12,250
There's a rumor that Dr. Bonten froze up
during the operation.

37
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:15,410
He must be on pins and needles now...

38
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,466
Hey, look. God Hand's walking by.

39
00:03:20,506 --> 00:03:24,120
There's a 99 percent chance he'll freak out.

40
00:03:27,756 --> 00:03:29,870
Mr. Fink has something he'd like to say.

41
00:03:51,176 --> 00:03:56,329
I hope for this hospital to save
more lives in the future.

42
00:03:56,409 --> 00:03:58,171
So I have a proposal.

43
00:04:02,873 --> 00:04:04,078
What?!

44
00:04:21,703 --> 00:04:22,943
The deficit?

45
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:27,210
Yes. It seems Fink was concerned
about our hospital's deficit.

46
00:04:27,970 --> 00:04:31,970
No point in donating if it just covers
the deficit, right?

47
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:33,805
The ER is causing the deficit.

48
00:04:34,110 --> 00:04:37,810
We can't let them take more critical patients
and worsen the deficit.

49
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:41,370
Not possible with Ashura around.
No way. I mean...

50
00:04:42,009 --> 00:04:45,563
She accepts every patient
without discrimination.

51
00:04:45,890 --> 00:04:48,830
We need to do something about her.

52
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:04,630
Don't worry about what others are saying.

53
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:09,390
You're one of the doctors
who saved Fink's life, Bonten.

54
00:05:11,036 --> 00:05:12,236
No...

55
00:05:13,263 --> 00:05:16,770
I'm a fake God Hand.

56
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:21,403
I should come clean to the public,

57
00:05:22,516 --> 00:05:25,423
but I can't do that to my family.

58
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:31,076
This is what I deserve.
I brought it on myself.

59
00:05:32,909 --> 00:05:35,256
It may have been a lie,

60
00:05:35,296 --> 00:05:40,770
but your knowledge and experience
as a cardiac surgeon are real.

61
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:51,030
Director, what brings you here?

62
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:54,510
I came to give you all a word of warning.

63
00:05:54,602 --> 00:05:56,029
A warning?

64
00:05:56,170 --> 00:05:58,704
I'm sure you're all aware of this already...

65
00:06:00,056 --> 00:06:04,690
We never accept critical patients.
That is this hospital's rule.

66
00:06:05,423 --> 00:06:08,410
I expect everyone to comply with this rule.

67
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:14,210
But following that rule means
we can't save lives we should be saving.

68
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:19,150
If we overextend and make mistakes,
the hospital's finances will only worsen.

69
00:06:20,030 --> 00:06:22,710
Then saving lives will be
out of the question entirely.

70
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:27,230
The lives saved by the ER are
certainly precious.

71
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:35,435
But as director, I have a duty to protect
the many lives this entire hospital saves.

72
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:41,940
By the way, I don't see Dr. Anno anywhere.

73
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:45,413
That was the best ramen I've ever had.

74
00:06:47,586 --> 00:06:50,798
Oh, there's something I wanted to ask you.

75
00:06:52,486 --> 00:06:55,720
Can you teach me some tips for intubation?

76
00:07:01,603 --> 00:07:02,810
Weird.

77
00:07:02,945 --> 00:07:05,781
Oh, sorry. I haven't managed
to do it successfully yet.

78
00:07:05,821 --> 00:07:07,190
The aftertaste is different.

79
00:07:07,230 --> 00:07:08,375
Oh, the ramen.

80
00:07:08,415 --> 00:07:09,669
Call an ambulance.

81
00:07:11,483 --> 00:07:12,683
Huh?

82
00:07:15,123 --> 00:07:17,010
I knew you had symptoms. Since when?

83
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:19,950
Shut up. This'll heal on its own.

84
00:07:20,036 --> 00:07:21,316
I'll roll you on your back.

85
00:07:22,496 --> 00:07:23,496
It's urgent!

86
00:07:23,523 --> 00:07:28,750
Dr. Yakushiji called. Dr. Anno is bringing
in an acute myocardial infarction patient.

87
00:07:32,063 --> 00:07:35,309
- PCI now. Contact the catheterization lab.
- Understood.

88
00:07:36,936 --> 00:07:39,596
Send that patient to another hospital.

89
00:07:39,636 --> 00:07:40,836
What are you saying? Move.

90
00:07:40,876 --> 00:07:41,876
We need to treat him now.

91
00:07:41,910 --> 00:07:46,610
We don't accept critical patients.
That's our rule. No exceptions.

92
00:07:46,650 --> 00:07:49,990
But the patient is suffering
right in front of us!

93
00:07:50,090 --> 00:07:53,310
Then you'd better hurry
and find another hospital.

94
00:07:53,350 --> 00:07:56,290
You call yourself a doctor?
He'll die if we do that.

95
00:07:56,482 --> 00:08:00,289
- Then this patient was just unlucky.
- That's inhuman.

96
00:08:00,329 --> 00:08:02,990
- Talking to you is pointless. Let's go.
- Yes!

97
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:05,470
Stop! That's an order from the director!

98
00:08:07,009 --> 00:08:08,242
Out of my way!

99
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,740
Damn it! ER-obsessed idiots!

100
00:08:17,299 --> 00:08:18,353
Sorry for the wait.

101
00:08:18,393 --> 00:08:19,603
Thanks.

102
00:08:20,079 --> 00:08:22,246
Next, uh, file those papers over there.

103
00:08:22,826 --> 00:08:24,061
Understood.

104
00:08:27,030 --> 00:08:30,476
Wow, Dr. Bonten, you're amazing.

105
00:08:31,710 --> 00:08:34,830
It seems surgery requests are coming in
from all over the world.

106
00:08:35,057 --> 00:08:36,249
As expected of God Hand.

107
00:08:36,289 --> 00:08:39,522
No, that's not it!
That's not what I mean at all.

108
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:43,210
Those poor patients.

109
00:08:43,550 --> 00:08:50,730
Who'd have thought that God Hand,
their last hope, turned out to be a fake?

110
00:08:54,245 --> 00:08:55,350
Director, what's wrong?

111
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:58,810
Stop Dr. Anno right now.
She's in the catheterization lab.

112
00:09:00,557 --> 00:09:02,270
Ashura! What are you doing?!

113
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:06,436
Unstable angina progressed to acute MI.
I'm revascularizing with PCI now.

114
00:09:06,476 --> 00:09:07,476
- What?!
- Hurry.

115
00:09:07,510 --> 00:09:08,770
- Right.
- This woman...

116
00:09:08,810 --> 00:09:10,963
- Wait, the PCI is canceled.
- Huh?

117
00:09:11,210 --> 00:09:14,050
This patient was under observation
in the surgery department.

118
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:17,930
A recent coronary angiography revealed
stenosis in two vessels.

119
00:09:17,970 --> 00:09:19,216
- Is that true?
- It's true.

120
00:09:19,256 --> 00:09:20,730
So, PCI can't be performed?

121
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:23,970
PCI risks restenosis.
My team will do a bypass.

122
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:25,750
No bypass. We're doing PCI.

123
00:09:25,790 --> 00:09:27,490
You just don't want to hand him over.

124
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:31,190
Dr. Anno, maybe surgery would be better...

125
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,870
He's right. We should leave it
to the attending physician.

126
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:38,290
Are you okay? I'll treat you right away.
Don't worry!

127
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,920
I will...

128
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:56,416
leave it to you.

129
00:10:07,742 --> 00:10:11,389
Dr. Ashura

130
00:10:14,693 --> 00:10:15,893
PCI.

131
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:19,141
Percutaneous Coronary Intervention.

132
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:23,911
It’s a treatment that uses a catheter
to place a stent and expand a blocked vessel.

133
00:10:24,936 --> 00:10:29,286
A catheter inserted through the wrist is
advanced to the heart's entrance.

134
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,832
Once the catheter reaches the heart,

135
00:10:31,872 --> 00:10:36,000
contrast dye identifies
which vessels are narrowed.

136
00:10:36,018 --> 00:10:40,860
Then a balloon dilates them, and a stent is
placed to restore blood flow.

137
00:10:45,863 --> 00:10:48,836
- Coronary artery reached. Inject contrast.
- Got it.

138
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:55,030
The left main coronary artery has
99 percent stenosis.

139
00:10:55,290 --> 00:10:58,770
Hemodynamic collapse is imminent.
Bypass is the only option.

140
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:03,030
Insert the guidewire. We'll check
vessel status with intravascular ultrasound.

141
00:11:06,230 --> 00:11:07,276
BP's dropping.

142
00:11:07,316 --> 00:11:08,750
Anno, what do we do?

143
00:11:09,323 --> 00:11:10,776
Ugh.

144
00:11:17,459 --> 00:11:18,659
Get the IABP ready.

145
00:11:19,096 --> 00:11:20,096
What?

146
00:11:20,123 --> 00:11:23,240
We stabilize blood pressure with IABP,
then do PCI.

147
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,640
Too risky.
Even specialists struggle with this.

148
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,300
You'd betray the patient's trust?

149
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:29,020
Anno, let's be careful here.

150
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:33,000
He said, "I will leave it to you." That means
giving him the best treatment possible.

151
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:39,260
On this battlefield,
it's always left up to us.

152
00:11:43,735 --> 00:11:45,079
IABP's ready.

153
00:11:45,519 --> 00:11:46,749
Let's do this.

154
00:11:50,403 --> 00:11:52,049
- Start pumping.
- Got it.

155
00:12:01,373 --> 00:12:02,593
Blood pressure's back.

156
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:05,743
- Inflate balloon and deploy stent.
- Right.

157
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:12,380
The slightest slip could be catastrophic.

158
00:12:22,016 --> 00:12:23,223
Incredible.

159
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:27,510
- Connect it.
- Right.

160
00:12:31,770 --> 00:12:33,736
- Inflate.
- Right.

161
00:12:39,963 --> 00:12:41,409
- Once more.
- Right.

162
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:56,130
Blood flow's restored!

163
00:12:56,955 --> 00:12:58,169
Incredible!

164
00:12:58,570 --> 00:12:59,803
Bravo!

165
00:13:00,690 --> 00:13:04,130
No, that's not it. Treating my patient
without permission? Unbelievable.

166
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:07,616
Dr. Kongo.

167
00:13:07,950 --> 00:13:10,403
- We'll treat the other vessels, too.
- Right.

168
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:18,730
Once the ER closure is official,
we can start building the new hospital.

169
00:13:18,950 --> 00:13:20,616
Well, that's good news.

170
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:26,750
I will make the new hospital a success
and return to Touou University Hospital.

171
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:30,838
I actually have some good news about that.

172
00:13:30,930 --> 00:13:36,316
Professor Takahashi in Thoracic Surgery is
stepping down due to poor health.

173
00:13:36,356 --> 00:13:37,356
What?

174
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:40,310
We'll be holding a professor selection soon.

175
00:13:40,763 --> 00:13:42,743
Please, let me run for it.

176
00:13:42,783 --> 00:13:48,570
But most professors on this
selection committee are from rival factions.

177
00:13:49,230 --> 00:13:54,490
Winning their votes will require some...
appropriate preparations.

178
00:13:54,709 --> 00:13:56,055
Understood.

179
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,936
"Appropriate preparations," huh.

180
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:12,780
Good work. We'll move you to a ward
and monitor your progress.

181
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:16,213
When can I go home?

182
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,576
Two or three days.

183
00:14:18,780 --> 00:14:24,200
That fast? They told me
surgery would take three weeks.

184
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:29,380
With PCI, the wound is smaller
than after surgery, so recovery is quicker.

185
00:14:30,060 --> 00:14:32,700
Huh. That's a relief.

186
00:14:32,993 --> 00:14:35,520
Yes. Well then, take care.

187
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:43,470
I'm glad the treatment went well,
but Dr. Kongo's gonna be furious.

188
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:49,590
Damn it! Those dead-weight freeloaders are
getting cocky! Damn it!

189
00:14:52,130 --> 00:14:54,483
Should we go apologize?

190
00:14:54,570 --> 00:14:57,390
- Positioning is key for intubation.
- Huh?

191
00:14:57,430 --> 00:15:02,183
Align the ear canal and sternum
at the same height. It'll go in easier.

192
00:15:05,859 --> 00:15:07,059
Why now?

193
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:15,036
So you're the famous Dr. Ashura?

194
00:15:16,109 --> 00:15:17,315
Who are you?

195
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:23,533
Since this is our first time meeting,
it's natural that you don't remember me.

196
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:29,700
I watched you perform PCI.
Impressive skills, just as they say.

197
00:15:30,553 --> 00:15:31,760
Thanks.

198
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:35,973
But an ER doctor doing
cardiac catheterization? That's unheard of.

199
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:41,280
Couldn't the attending physician have
saved the patient just as well?

200
00:15:46,093 --> 00:15:47,483
His life, sure.

201
00:15:58,950 --> 00:16:03,436
But why did
that patient specifically request Dr. Anno?

202
00:16:03,496 --> 00:16:07,596
He was brought into our ER once before.

203
00:16:07,636 --> 00:16:09,190
Oh, really?

204
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:12,902
He came in with unstable angina.

205
00:16:12,942 --> 00:16:18,170
Dr. Anno treated him and handed him off
to Surgery, but he checked out fast.

206
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,716
Without treatment?

207
00:16:19,756 --> 00:16:22,069
Said he couldn't rest with customers waiting.

208
00:16:23,410 --> 00:16:28,250
Dr. Ashura started visiting
his restaurant regularly after that.

209
00:16:29,016 --> 00:16:32,856
So that's why she insisted on PCI,
the one with the shorter hospital stay.

210
00:16:33,950 --> 00:16:39,990
She may seem focused only on emergencies,
but she truly cares about the patients.

211
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,220
What is this about?

212
00:16:52,519 --> 00:16:54,232
You know...

213
00:16:55,032 --> 00:16:59,813
A professor selection is coming up
at Touou University Hospital soon.

214
00:17:01,153 --> 00:17:04,480
I plan to run, of course,

215
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:11,720
but as you know, the professor selection
at Touou Hospital is no simple matter.

216
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:17,896
So I'd like you to lend me a hand.

217
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:19,671
Huh?

218
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,913
Could you introduce me

219
00:17:24,146 --> 00:17:28,580
to cardiac surgery professors
who might vote for me?

220
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:32,240
Of course, I wouldn't ask you
to do it for free.

221
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:40,868
I can't help you with anything dishonest...

222
00:17:40,908 --> 00:17:47,650
Are you sure about that? I could fire you
and expose the truth right now.

223
00:17:48,490 --> 00:17:52,170
Your face and name are now known
around the world.

224
00:17:53,416 --> 00:17:56,976
Forget being a doctor,
you wouldn't be able to find any work at all.

225
00:17:57,383 --> 00:17:59,536
Your family will be out on the streets.

226
00:17:59,683 --> 00:18:00,683
That's...

227
00:18:00,710 --> 00:18:04,290
You've clawed your way up using
dirty tricks all this time, haven't you?

228
00:18:05,390 --> 00:18:07,830
Why would you hesitate now?

229
00:18:08,970 --> 00:18:14,863
Just follow my instructions,
and I'll make it worth your while.

230
00:18:24,419 --> 00:18:26,219
Huh? Dr. Tamon!

231
00:18:27,505 --> 00:18:29,605
- Vice Director!
- Is Anno here?

232
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:31,733
Dr. Anno?

233
00:18:36,141 --> 00:18:37,141
What do you want?

234
00:18:37,173 --> 00:18:38,403
Got a minute?

235
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:47,670
To secure Fink's donation for the hospital,
we must eliminate the deficit now.

236
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:50,430
You mean we should fix the ER's deficit.

237
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:55,030
No matter what anyone says,
I will never turn away a patient.

238
00:18:55,663 --> 00:18:58,536
I can't abandon patients
because of some new hospital.

239
00:19:00,169 --> 00:19:03,430
- And I won't allow shutting down the ER...
- Too late.

240
00:19:04,530 --> 00:19:10,250
The chairwoman decided
that the ER will be closed in two months.

241
00:19:18,276 --> 00:19:20,360
Well, this is rare. What's the matter?

242
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:24,090
Don't play dumb!
What do you mean, closing the ER?

243
00:19:26,013 --> 00:19:28,573
This place is so dreary.

244
00:19:29,986 --> 00:19:31,360
Let's go somewhere else.

245
00:19:36,183 --> 00:19:43,443
When you were a resident, we'd come here
all the time, and I'd listen to you vent.

246
00:19:46,150 --> 00:19:48,556
Are you seriously going to shut down the ER?

247
00:19:50,139 --> 00:19:51,350
Yes.

248
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:56,140
If Taishaku loses its ER,
lives we could've saved will be lost.

249
00:19:56,693 --> 00:19:59,140
- Of course, I understand that.
- Then why?

250
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:01,840
I have a mission more important than that.

251
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:11,626
The new hospital will have cutting-edge
facilities and the best staff available.

252
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:16,200
We'll save patients
that Taishaku never could before.

253
00:20:20,490 --> 00:20:24,910
If I could, I would have kept the ER, too.

254
00:20:26,090 --> 00:20:28,395
I'm sure Dr. Tamon feels the same way.

255
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:29,648
No, he doesn't.

256
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:32,456
He chose the new hospital over the ER, too.

257
00:20:32,496 --> 00:20:35,590
He has a mission he needs to fulfill.

258
00:20:36,822 --> 00:20:38,036
A mission?

259
00:20:39,550 --> 00:20:45,250
Have you ever heard
about Dr. Tamon's experiences overseas?

260
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:47,870
What?

261
00:20:48,490 --> 00:20:51,310
Saving people in conflict zones.

262
00:20:52,936 --> 00:20:54,916
It's easy to say you can,

263
00:20:55,516 --> 00:21:01,582
but even with his skills,
he couldn't save most of them.

264
00:21:03,529 --> 00:21:04,736
Why not?

265
00:21:05,236 --> 00:21:12,536
With no medicine, blood, or equipment,
there's barely anything a doctor can do.

266
00:21:15,450 --> 00:21:20,410
Still, he refused to give up
and tried to continue his work.

267
00:21:21,823 --> 00:21:25,269
But his organization was
on the verge of shutting down

268
00:21:26,449 --> 00:21:30,176
due to a lack of funding.

269
00:21:31,863 --> 00:21:36,730
That's why he came back to Japan
and became my right hand.

270
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:40,403
In exchange, he wanted

271
00:21:40,663 --> 00:21:43,763
some of the new hospital's profits
to be used for overseas aid.

272
00:21:51,713 --> 00:21:53,518
Even so, I...

273
00:21:56,030 --> 00:22:00,830
I will never let anyone abandon the ER.

274
00:22:34,570 --> 00:22:36,596
Professor, how about another drink?

275
00:22:36,636 --> 00:22:38,530
Well, don't mind if I do.

276
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:45,838
Dr. Bonten's work has been
quite the talk at Touou University Hospital.

277
00:22:46,336 --> 00:22:50,143
We were just regretting
letting such a talent slip away.

278
00:22:50,183 --> 00:22:54,670
Steve Fink's recent operation was
truly remarkable.

279
00:22:55,122 --> 00:22:57,496
I would have loved to see it myself.

280
00:23:00,180 --> 00:23:04,995
By the way, I've prepared
a small gift for you.

281
00:23:05,035 --> 00:23:06,253
A gift?

282
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:15,003
If it's to your liking, I'd be grateful
for your support in the next professor vote.

283
00:23:25,143 --> 00:23:28,570
He's canceling the donation?
What's going on?

284
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:31,350
He wouldn't give us a detailed reason.

285
00:23:32,710 --> 00:23:35,410
Did we do something wrong?

286
00:23:37,350 --> 00:23:41,169
Maybe the deficit issue was
the problem after all.

287
00:23:41,209 --> 00:23:45,970
No, I told him we'd close the ER,
but that didn't seem to be the reason.

288
00:23:46,010 --> 00:23:47,450
Then what is it?

289
00:23:47,490 --> 00:23:49,250
Panicking won't help.

290
00:23:51,350 --> 00:23:54,083
I'll figure out a way to convince Fink.

291
00:23:55,849 --> 00:23:59,550
Dr. Bonten, Mr. Fink is asking for you.

292
00:24:01,916 --> 00:24:03,123
Come in.

293
00:24:13,955 --> 00:24:19,049
He changed his mind about the donation?
I mean, why would he do that?

294
00:24:19,070 --> 00:24:21,296
We don't know yet.

295
00:24:21,336 --> 00:24:25,370
What a shame. You were just one step away
from becoming the new hospital's director.

296
00:24:25,470 --> 00:24:27,850
That doesn't matter now.

297
00:24:31,101 --> 00:24:32,309
Come in.

298
00:24:35,197 --> 00:24:38,023
It's rare for you to pay me a visit.

299
00:24:38,970 --> 00:24:41,810
It's about the donation from Fink.

300
00:24:43,523 --> 00:24:44,736
What happened?

301
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:51,293
The reason Fink withdrew the donation...

302
00:25:33,453 --> 00:25:34,603
Taro Bonten

303
00:25:34,643 --> 00:25:38,869
The director is using money to win
the professor election through bribery.

304
00:25:38,923 --> 00:25:40,762
He asked me to introduce him

305
00:25:41,329 --> 00:25:43,875
to a cardiac surgery professor.

306
00:25:45,255 --> 00:25:50,695
I had no idea the money was embezzled.
I'm truly sorry.

307
00:25:54,107 --> 00:25:55,307
No.

308
00:25:56,539 --> 00:25:58,155
You have nothing to apologize for.

309
00:25:58,195 --> 00:26:00,088
But I could have refused.

310
00:26:00,626 --> 00:26:03,806
I'm the one who didn't.

311
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:06,620
I’m quitting medicine.

312
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:09,111
I'm going to submit my resignation.

313
00:26:09,151 --> 00:26:10,860
Wait. You can't do that...

314
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:12,659
Let me take responsibility.

315
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,621
After everything that happened,

316
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:21,180
trying to continue practicing medicine was
a mistake from the start.

317
00:26:33,420 --> 00:26:35,680
Snuck out of work again?

318
00:26:37,180 --> 00:26:38,500
It's my day off.

319
00:26:39,620 --> 00:26:42,300
Dressed like that? Some day off.

320
00:26:42,993 --> 00:26:44,953
You went in on your own again, huh?

321
00:26:45,099 --> 00:26:47,900
Nothing to do at home.
The hospital's where I feel at ease.

322
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:50,280
A born workaholic.

323
00:26:50,299 --> 00:26:51,519
So are you.

324
00:26:59,919 --> 00:27:01,189
How is it?

325
00:27:02,799 --> 00:27:03,999
Same as always.

326
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:08,800
All thanks to your treatment.

327
00:27:14,750 --> 00:27:16,030
Thanks for the meal.

328
00:27:18,702 --> 00:27:19,969
Thank you.

329
00:27:21,136 --> 00:27:24,896
You came to check on my health, right?

330
00:27:27,310 --> 00:27:28,850
I was just hungry.

331
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,440
Good work today, sir.

332
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:44,380
If it means returning to Touou Hospital,
no effort is too great.

333
00:27:44,946 --> 00:27:47,820
Dirty tactics or not,
I have no choice but to use them.

334
00:27:48,260 --> 00:27:49,480
Dirty tactics?

335
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:56,120
Yes. But even if it's discovered,
I've made sure I won't be caught.

336
00:27:56,820 --> 00:28:00,580
As expected of you, Director.
All part of the plan.

337
00:28:01,093 --> 00:28:03,913
Once I'm back at Touou Hospital,
I'll become hospital director.

338
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:07,160
The highest authority in Japanese medicine.

339
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:11,840
A doctor's worth can only be measured
by authority.

340
00:28:23,809 --> 00:28:25,016
Incoming.

341
00:28:32,394 --> 00:28:33,594
Yes!

342
00:28:34,910 --> 00:28:36,980
What? The director?

343
00:29:07,970 --> 00:29:10,810
Head-on collision with a truck.
Steel pipe impaled in the abdomen.

344
00:29:11,256 --> 00:29:13,110
Treat me now!

345
00:29:13,150 --> 00:29:15,570
- Get both patients to the ER now!
- Got it!

346
00:29:19,582 --> 00:29:20,796
Dr. Tamon.

347
00:29:21,550 --> 00:29:24,270
Transfer them
to another hospital immediately.

348
00:29:24,955 --> 00:29:27,009
- What?
- We don't accept critical patients.

349
00:29:27,563 --> 00:29:29,263
That's our hospital's rule.

350
00:29:30,539 --> 00:29:32,839
There’s no guarantee
we’ll find another hospital in time.

351
00:29:32,879 --> 00:29:37,970
The director himself ordered us
to turn away such patients.

352
00:29:39,829 --> 00:29:43,930
But if we don't treat him now, he'll die!

353
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:46,470
Dr. Daikoku, let's get him inside.

354
00:29:46,510 --> 00:29:47,763
Right, let's go.

355
00:29:51,469 --> 00:29:52,942
Dr. Daikoku.

356
00:29:54,949 --> 00:29:56,469
Don't you agree?

357
00:30:03,913 --> 00:30:05,133
Dr. Daikoku.

358
00:30:06,385 --> 00:30:09,765
We don't accept critical patients.
That's our rule.

359
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:18,116
Dr. Daikoku, we need to move now!

360
00:30:22,986 --> 00:30:24,282
Forgive me.

361
00:30:27,203 --> 00:30:29,289
I'm sorry.

362
00:30:31,017 --> 00:30:32,297
Please.

363
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:36,156
Save me.

364
00:30:37,742 --> 00:30:40,915
Someone who exploits this hospital
for personal gain has...

365
00:30:43,496 --> 00:30:45,409
no value worth saving.

366
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:52,283
What do we do?

367
00:30:58,090 --> 00:30:59,850
"No value worth saving?"

368
00:31:14,389 --> 00:31:15,635
Dr. Anno!

369
00:31:15,990 --> 00:31:17,550
I'll take you on.

370
00:31:20,379 --> 00:31:21,672
I knew you'd come.

371
00:31:22,153 --> 00:31:24,579
I don't care about value. I'm saving them.

372
00:31:26,113 --> 00:31:30,381
This man embezzled hospital funds
to get back to Touou University Hospital.

373
00:31:31,020 --> 00:31:34,851
He spread that money around
to buy his way in.

374
00:31:34,891 --> 00:31:36,184
So what?

375
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:41,796
Because of him,

376
00:31:43,810 --> 00:31:46,240
the new hospital has been
set back indefinitely.

377
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:48,880
Abandoning a life right in front of you
for your own goals.

378
00:31:50,429 --> 00:31:51,713
You're no different.

379
00:31:55,416 --> 00:31:56,616
That's not true.

380
00:31:57,450 --> 00:31:59,336
- I'm...
- This is a battlefield!

381
00:32:01,543 --> 00:32:03,996
Anyone who picks which lives
to save has no place here!

382
00:32:10,312 --> 00:32:11,516
You're in the way.

383
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:15,016
- Kid, get them inside.
- Got it!

384
00:32:18,310 --> 00:32:19,690
I'm an emergency physician.

385
00:32:20,410 --> 00:32:25,810
No matter who's asking for help,
I have a duty to save their life.

386
00:32:33,900 --> 00:32:35,879
I'll take the driver. The director's yours.

387
00:32:35,919 --> 00:32:37,219
- Got it.
- On three.

388
00:32:37,259 --> 00:32:38,520
One, two, three.

389
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:40,510
- Prep the patient.
- Attaching monitor.

390
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:42,225
Remove the coverings.

391
00:32:42,979 --> 00:32:44,940
- Can you hear me?
- What do we do?

392
00:32:44,980 --> 00:32:48,066
Removing the pipe could cause
massive bleeding if the artery’s damaged.

393
00:32:48,106 --> 00:32:50,333
We open the abdomen, stop the bleeding,
then remove it.

394
00:32:50,373 --> 00:32:51,373
Understood.

395
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,953
- I'll cut the clothes.
- Got it.

396
00:32:57,840 --> 00:33:01,160
Do you know who I am?

397
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,360
He's becoming agitated.

398
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:03,980
Director, please calm down.

399
00:33:04,286 --> 00:33:05,616
Hold him down, now!

400
00:33:06,206 --> 00:33:09,685
I'm going back to Touou University Hospital,

401
00:33:10,739 --> 00:33:13,986
and no one can stop me!

402
00:33:19,506 --> 00:33:20,766
Arterial damage.

403
00:33:21,493 --> 00:33:22,505
Asystole.

404
00:33:22,545 --> 00:33:24,611
- We need to stop the bleeding.
- Got it!

405
00:33:25,660 --> 00:33:27,560
- Kid, intubate with the light.
- Got it!

406
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:29,579
- Get adrenaline and blood ready.
- Got it.

407
00:33:30,026 --> 00:33:31,493
- Intubating.
- Yes.

408
00:33:31,506 --> 00:33:33,836
- Prep the ultrasound, we'll need it next.
- Got it.

409
00:33:42,610 --> 00:33:44,170
- Intubating now.
- Yes.

410
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:58,920
Align the ear canal and sternum
at the same height.

411
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:01,640
The ear canal and sternum are
at the same height.

412
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:04,220
- Tube, please.
- Here.

413
00:34:12,889 --> 00:34:14,969
Good, it's in.

414
00:34:15,423 --> 00:34:16,530
Connecting the ventilator.

415
00:34:16,570 --> 00:34:17,670
Anno, we've got trouble.

416
00:34:17,710 --> 00:34:19,236
- Kid, take over.
- Got it!

417
00:34:22,580 --> 00:34:24,220
Massive pericardial bleeding.

418
00:34:24,303 --> 00:34:25,399
Cardiac tamponade.

419
00:34:25,439 --> 00:34:27,006
Traumatic cardiac rupture.

420
00:34:27,346 --> 00:34:30,573
We need a cardiac surgeon to operate.

421
00:34:31,739 --> 00:34:34,284
All cardiac surgeons are in surgery
and unavailable.

422
00:34:34,324 --> 00:34:37,609
He'll die without immediate surgery.
What do we do?

423
00:34:53,023 --> 00:34:54,150
Dr. Bonten.

424
00:34:54,190 --> 00:34:56,150
Leave him to me.

425
00:34:56,216 --> 00:34:58,595
Dr. Anno, please handle the director.

426
00:34:58,635 --> 00:35:00,849
Have you ever done
a heart rupture surgery before?

427
00:35:01,862 --> 00:35:03,082
No.

428
00:35:03,929 --> 00:35:05,195
Can you really do this?

429
00:35:06,576 --> 00:35:11,690
I'm not God Hand.
I don't have a 99 percent success rate.

430
00:35:12,096 --> 00:35:14,770
I'm just an ordinary doctor.

431
00:35:17,176 --> 00:35:20,490
But still, I am a cardiac surgeon.

432
00:35:21,350 --> 00:35:24,290
I will save him. I swear it.

433
00:35:28,287 --> 00:35:30,113
- Laparotomy to stop the bleeding.
- Got it.

434
00:35:30,153 --> 00:35:31,625
Dr. Bonten, I'll assist you.

435
00:35:31,665 --> 00:35:32,925
Thank you.

436
00:35:36,333 --> 00:35:37,659
Suction.

437
00:35:46,016 --> 00:35:47,222
Beat.

438
00:35:50,036 --> 00:35:52,843
Where is the bleeding source?

439
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:56,453
There’s massive blood in the pericardium.

440
00:35:56,493 --> 00:35:59,306
- I'll cut it to drain the blood.
- Understood.

441
00:35:59,346 --> 00:36:00,680
- Scalpel.
- Here.

442
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:02,280
- Forceps.
- Here.

443
00:36:03,905 --> 00:36:05,106
It's bleeding!

444
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:13,500
Doctor, BP's in the 30s!

445
00:36:25,846 --> 00:36:27,903
- Show me the incision.
- Got it.

446
00:36:27,943 --> 00:36:29,143
- Gauze.
- Here.

447
00:36:36,163 --> 00:36:37,363
Beat.

448
00:36:38,583 --> 00:36:39,783
Beat.

449
00:36:40,769 --> 00:36:41,873
Beat.

450
00:36:41,913 --> 00:36:43,383
- Suction.
- Yes.

451
00:36:48,383 --> 00:36:49,883
The bleeding's from here.

452
00:36:49,890 --> 00:36:51,182
- Gauze.
- Here.

453
00:36:51,515 --> 00:36:52,715
Please!

454
00:36:55,590 --> 00:36:57,349
Come on, beat.

455
00:37:18,416 --> 00:37:20,116
Heartbeat's back!

456
00:37:20,300 --> 00:37:21,436
Suction. Start more blood.

457
00:37:21,476 --> 00:37:22,683
- Yes!
- Yes!

458
00:37:23,711 --> 00:37:24,918
Where?

459
00:37:25,573 --> 00:37:26,778
Where?

460
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:29,206
Where is it?

461
00:37:29,832 --> 00:37:32,852
Placing a felt-pledgeted mattress suture.

462
00:37:40,662 --> 00:37:41,922
So fast.

463
00:37:42,523 --> 00:37:44,150
Not a single wasted movement.

464
00:37:44,910 --> 00:37:46,250
Perfect technique.

465
00:37:52,679 --> 00:37:53,882
Done.

466
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:57,180
Good. No bleeding.

467
00:37:57,473 --> 00:37:58,820
Suturing the pericardium.

468
00:37:59,166 --> 00:38:00,599
Give me 3-0 Vicryl, please.

469
00:38:00,639 --> 00:38:01,845
Here.

470
00:38:02,426 --> 00:38:03,626
Where?

471
00:38:04,459 --> 00:38:05,679
Where is it?

472
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:10,270
Found it.

473
00:38:11,036 --> 00:38:12,296
The kidney.

474
00:38:12,493 --> 00:38:14,000
He can survive with one kidney.

475
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,936
- Removing it. Satinsky clamp.
- Here.

476
00:38:18,599 --> 00:38:21,272
- Aortic cross-clamp off.
- Got it.

477
00:38:29,813 --> 00:38:31,143
I will save you.

478
00:39:06,298 --> 00:39:07,567
Director!

479
00:39:09,879 --> 00:39:11,084
Director!

480
00:39:14,862 --> 00:39:16,108
You're safe...

481
00:39:17,715 --> 00:39:19,716
Thank goodness you're safe.

482
00:39:22,306 --> 00:39:23,766
Ah, Chairwoman.

483
00:39:25,146 --> 00:39:27,486
I wasn't sure how it would turn out,

484
00:39:28,465 --> 00:39:29,692
but he pulled through.

485
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:33,200
I'm so, so relieved.

486
00:39:34,103 --> 00:39:35,796
Embezzlement...

487
00:39:37,830 --> 00:39:40,843
He really did whatever he pleased.

488
00:39:42,110 --> 00:39:43,476
Huh? Embezzlement?

489
00:39:43,770 --> 00:39:46,790
I wanted to keep things quiet,

490
00:39:47,536 --> 00:39:49,456
but we need to drain all the pus.

491
00:39:50,130 --> 00:39:51,130
Huh?

492
00:39:51,156 --> 00:39:52,850
I'm calling the police.

493
00:39:53,669 --> 00:39:54,950
I'll make sure

494
00:39:55,549 --> 00:39:57,150
he pays for his crimes.

495
00:39:58,063 --> 00:39:59,330
What?!

496
00:40:00,550 --> 00:40:02,016
So, Dr. Kongo...

497
00:40:02,549 --> 00:40:04,129
Tell him when he wakes up.

498
00:40:05,189 --> 00:40:07,949
Wait, please!
The shock could stop his heart again!

499
00:40:08,689 --> 00:40:10,143
If that happens,

500
00:40:10,789 --> 00:40:12,735
ask Ashura to save him again.

501
00:40:12,775 --> 00:40:13,850
Good point!

502
00:40:13,890 --> 00:40:16,603
No, no, wait! That's not it! That's not it!

503
00:40:18,883 --> 00:40:20,363
Thank you for everything.

504
00:40:21,010 --> 00:40:26,290
Everyone, I'm truly sorry
about what happened.

505
00:40:28,496 --> 00:40:31,570
I did something unforgivable

506
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:35,423
to the ER staff.

507
00:40:36,710 --> 00:40:39,810
I am deeply sorry.

508
00:40:45,229 --> 00:40:46,756
To take responsibility,

509
00:40:48,090 --> 00:40:50,308
I will no longer...

510
00:40:52,570 --> 00:40:55,309
- I'm going to quit being a doctor.
- What?

511
00:40:56,663 --> 00:40:59,310
In the end, thanks to all of you...

512
00:41:00,209 --> 00:41:02,010
I got to act like a real doctor.

513
00:41:03,616 --> 00:41:05,362
- Thank you.
- Please, wait.

514
00:41:06,209 --> 00:41:08,716
Why are you quitting?

515
00:41:08,730 --> 00:41:11,730
He's right! Today's surgery was incredible!

516
00:41:13,010 --> 00:41:14,343
I no longer have the right

517
00:41:15,616 --> 00:41:17,836
to continue as a doctor.

518
00:41:26,573 --> 00:41:28,013
It's indeed true,

519
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:31,060
you may have made mistakes.

520
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:34,660
But if you hadn't come,

521
00:41:35,143 --> 00:41:37,060
that driver would have died.

522
00:41:38,906 --> 00:41:42,840
Dr. Bonten, your surgery saved
the patient's life.

523
00:41:46,073 --> 00:41:47,533
With your skills,

524
00:41:48,266 --> 00:41:50,340
you can save many more patients.

525
00:41:51,055 --> 00:41:52,259
And that is

526
00:41:52,780 --> 00:41:55,700
something you can do to atone for your sins.

527
00:41:59,340 --> 00:42:01,940
If you have no place in Surgery,

528
00:42:02,713 --> 00:42:04,000
why not join the ER?

529
00:42:06,380 --> 00:42:07,880
- Huh?
- I mean it.

530
00:42:08,660 --> 00:42:10,640
Let's save patients here together.

531
00:42:14,193 --> 00:42:17,300
I also want to work with you, Dr. Bonten.

532
00:42:17,500 --> 00:42:21,056
We'd all feel reassured having you here.

533
00:42:23,646 --> 00:42:24,910
Anno, what do you think?

534
00:42:25,963 --> 00:42:27,170
Huh?

535
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:34,680
We're short-staffed,

536
00:42:35,123 --> 00:42:36,676
so more doctors can't hurt.

537
00:42:39,623 --> 00:42:40,916
In other words,

538
00:42:41,770 --> 00:42:44,043
she means you're welcome here.

539
00:42:44,083 --> 00:42:45,343
Hard to tell, right?

540
00:42:46,310 --> 00:42:47,930
Are you really sure?

541
00:42:47,970 --> 00:42:49,343
If you're willing,

542
00:42:50,150 --> 00:42:52,050
we'll welcome you anytime.

543
00:42:54,243 --> 00:42:55,516
Thank you.

544
00:42:55,916 --> 00:42:57,396
Oh, but...

545
00:42:58,130 --> 00:43:00,429
The ER is a battlefield every day.

546
00:43:00,469 --> 00:43:02,197
- Can you handle that?
- Huh?

547
00:43:02,237 --> 00:43:05,110
Tamotsu, don't say unnecessary things.

548
00:43:05,150 --> 00:43:06,430
But it's true.

549
00:43:06,470 --> 00:43:08,628
Tell him the ER is a wonderful place!

550
00:43:08,668 --> 00:43:10,776
I couldn't say that with a straight face.

551
00:43:10,816 --> 00:43:12,890
Why not? You always look like
you're having fun.

552
00:43:12,930 --> 00:43:14,810
No, I don't.

553
00:43:17,403 --> 00:43:19,650
- You love the ER, right?
- I do not.

554
00:43:20,352 --> 00:43:23,676
So you've finally decided
to come work with us.

555
00:43:25,270 --> 00:43:27,290
I was going to pick Touou Hospital,

556
00:43:27,790 --> 00:43:29,330
but you insisted so much, Yuri.

557
00:43:29,836 --> 00:43:31,056
I can't wait.

558
00:43:31,096 --> 00:43:33,450
But why emergency medicine for me?

559
00:43:33,690 --> 00:43:35,690
Taishaku has plastic surgery, too.

560
00:43:35,836 --> 00:43:37,483
It'll be fine.

561
00:43:37,496 --> 00:43:39,570
You're interested in what we do, aren't you?

562
00:43:40,170 --> 00:43:42,270
It just seemed a little interesting.

563
00:43:44,770 --> 00:43:51,490
Who knows? Maybe Ashura is
even more skilled than you are.

564
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:55,740
We'll see about that.

565
00:44:00,130 --> 00:44:02,116
I came to give you an answer.

566
00:44:09,598 --> 00:44:10,598
Next Episode Preview

567
00:44:10,623 --> 00:44:13,100
I'll be doing things my way.

568
00:44:13,149 --> 00:44:14,540
I said I don't need it!

569
00:44:14,640 --> 00:44:17,093
- We have no right to force treatment.
-
Right
?

570
00:44:17,133 --> 00:44:19,213
Aren't you afraid of failing?

571
00:44:19,253 --> 00:44:21,113
Didn't you want to save the ER?

572
00:44:21,153 --> 00:44:24,453
I don't just want to save their lives.
I want to protect their future as well.
